Step-1: Make data directories
=============================
Choose path where glycositeminer data will be stored
e.g /data/glycositeminer/	

	$ mkdir -p /data/glycositeminer/v-1.0
	$ rm rootdir
	$ rm reldir
	$ rm miscdir
	$ ln -s /data/glycositeminer rootdir
	$ ln -s /data/glycositeminer/v-1.0 reldir
	$ ln -s /data/glycositeminer/misc miscdir


Step-2: Data download
=====================
	The following download scripts will download data and place it under
	reldir/glygen/, reldir/medline_xml/, reldir/pubtator_downloads/
	and reldir/gene_info/. This assumes that all protein datasets have been
	created under /data/projects/glygen/generated/datasets/unreviewed/

	The download-medline.py script depends on the file conf/medline.json which needs
	to be edited. To adjust the values for the "baseline" section, go to 
	https://ftp.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/baseline/ and see the indexes of the 
	first and last pubmed*.xml.gz files. For example, if the first and last files are
	"pubmed25n0001.xml.gz" and "pubmed25n1274.xml.gz", then the base line section
	in conf/medline.json should be:
	{
		"baseline":{
			"url":"https://ftp.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/baseline/",
			"start":1,
			"end":1274,
     	 	"year":26
		}
	}
	The "updatefiles" section should be updated in the same manner by going to 
	https://ftp.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/updatefiles/
	

	$ python3 download-glygen.py
	$ python3 download-medline.py	
	$ python3 download-pubtator.py
	$ python3 download-gene-info.py



Step-3: Dump known sites
========================
	The following script creates reldir/glygen/known_sites.csv which
	contains known glycosylation sites assuming *_proteoform_glycosylation_sites_*.csv 
	datasets are created under /data/projects/glygen/generated/datasets/unreviewed/

	$ python3 extract-known-sites.py


Step-4: Processing medline download
===================================
	This is a wrapper around extract-medline-data.py which use NER model
	to find abstracts from xml files under reldir/medline_xml/
	that contain site and glyco entities
	  		
	$ python3 wrap-extract-medline-data.py
	
	- input
			reldir/medline_xml/*
			miscdir/glyco.json
	- output
			reldir/medline_extracts/*
			reldir/medline_abstracts/*
			logs/medline_abstracts.%s.%s.log
			



Step-5: Processing pubtator download
====================================
	$ python3 extract-pubtator-data.py
   - input
      	reldir/pubtator_downloads/bioconcepts2pubtatorcentral.offset.gz
   - output
         reldir/pubtator_extracts/*
         logs/pubtator_extracts.log



Step-6: Making LLM API calls
============================
   - description
      uses openai.com API to extract species, gene, site entities from
      abstracts in reldir/medline_abstracts/ and writes out entities JSON
      files under reldir/llm_entities/$BATCH/ where $BATCH is batch index (1, 2, 3).
      You can run this for more than one batches if you think the LLM output will 
		vary.
   - script
      python3 generate-llm-entities.py  -b $BATCH
   - input
         reldir/medline_abstracts/*
   - output
         reldir/llm_entities/$BATCH/llm.*.json


Step-7: Making entities
=======================
   - script
         make-entities.py
   - input
         reldir/medline_extracts/*.json
			reldir/pubtator_extracts/*.json
			reldir/glygen/*names*.csv
			reldir/glygen/*genelocus*.csv
			reldir/glygen/*geneid*.csv
			reldir/llm_entities/*/*.json
   		reldir/misc/aa.csv
			reldir/misc/known_sites.csv
	- output
         reldir/entities/site.*.json
			reldir/entities/glyco.*.json
			reldir/entities/species.*.json
			reldir/entities/gene.*.json
			reldir/entities/extragene.*.json


Step-8: Integrate entities
==========================
   - script
         integrate-entities.py
   - input
         reldir/entities/site.*.json
         reldir/entities/glyco.*.json
         reldir/entities/species.*.json
         reldir/entities/gene.*.json
         reldir/entities/extragene.*.json
